{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place olive oil, oregano and lemon zest in mixing bowl then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Place butterflied chicken breasts between two large pieces of cling film and flatten with a rolling pin. Place chicken in a dish and pour over marinade. Rinse mixing bowl.","Place a bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in yoghurt. Remove bowl and set aside.","Place courgette in mixing bowl and chop <b>Turbo\/0.5 sec\/1-2 times<b>. Tip out into a muslin cloth and squeeze out liquid. Stir squeezed courgette into yoghurt and adjust seasoning to taste. Set tzatziki aside in fridge.","Place 500 g water in mixing bowl. Preheat grill to 230°C.","Line Varoma dish with enough baking paper to come 2-3 cm up the sides, then place into position. Weigh in couscous, peas, olives, red peppers and spring onions. Sprinkle 75 g water over couscous and vegetables then stir with a fork to moisten. Cover Varoma  then steam <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Sprinkle another 50 g water over couscous and vegetables and stir well with a fork. Cover Varoma and steam again <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Meanwhile, grill marinated chicken for 5 minutes (230°C) on each side until browned.","Slice grilled chicken into strips and serve with couscous and tzatziki on the side."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["60 g olive oil","1 tsp dried oregano","½ lemon, finely grated zest only","3 chicken breasts, skinless, butterflied (sliced through horizontally almost to the edge then opened out)","200 g Greek yoghurt","1 courgette, cut in pieces, (approx. 150 g)","1 pinch fine sea salt, plus extra to taste","1 pinch ground black pepper, plus extra to taste","625 g water","250 g couscous","50 g frozen peas","50 g pitted black olives","50 g red peppers, diced","25 g spring onions, sliced (1 cm)"]}],"id":"r120834","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-LTnRFfroxZ8\/XZQw1iBJcfI\/AAAAAAAAcpc\/kCOAvNDR-C8NLt_81ernIx1pcEcYSey6wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_gozPi1spm3Sa_oFe.png","title":"Lemon Chicken with Couscous and Tzatziki","publishedAt":"2016-10-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"39.2 g","fat":"21.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"55.6 g","calories":"2384 kJ \/ 570 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, rolling pin, muslin or nut milk bag, baking paper, refrigerator, grill","hintsAndTricks":["The method in the recipe produces a lighter, steamed couscous. If you prefer, you can soak the couscous in 250 g water for 5 minutes then steam as directed in the recipe.","To butterfly a chicken breast, use a sharp knife to slice into one side of the breast, starting at the thicker end and ending at the thin point. Open out the breast so that it resembles a butterfly."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","30m","4 portions"]}